ts_Amendment&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D16" title=3D"Edit section: Rat=
ifications"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</=
span></span></div>
<p>On March 22, 1972, the ERA was placed before the state legislatures, wit=
h a seven-year deadline to acquire ratification by three-fourths (38) of th=
e state legislatures. A majority of states ratified the proposed constituti=
onal amendment within a year. Hawaii became the first state to ratify the E=
RA, which it did on the same day the amendment was approved by Congress: Th=
e U.S. Senate's vote on H.J.Res.&nbsp;208 took place in the mid-to-late aft=
ernoon in Washington, D.C., when it was still midday in Hawaii. The <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hawaii_Senate" title=3D"Hawaii Senate">Ha=
waii Senate</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hawaii_House_o=
f_Representatives" title=3D"Hawaii House of Representatives">House of Repre=
sentatives</a> voted their approval shortly after noon Hawaii Standard Time=
.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-97" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedi=
a.org/wiki/Equal_Rights_Amendment#cite_note-97"><span class=3D"cite-bracket=
">[</span>97<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-98" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Equal_=
Rights_Amendment#cite_note-98"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>98<span=
 class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>During 1972, a total of 22 state legislatures ratified the amendment=
 and eight more joined in early 1973. Between 1974 and 1977, only five stat=
es approved the ERA, and advocates became worried about the approaching Mar=
ch 22, 1979, deadline.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-ERA:_History_49-1" class=3D"refer=
ence"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Equal_Rights_Amendment#cite_=
note-ERA:_History-49"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>49<span class=3D=
"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_ref-99" class=3D"reference=
"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Equal_Rights_Amendment#cite_note=
-99"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>99<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]<=
/span></a></sup>
